==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: meretriciousness
<hw>mer`e*tri"cious*ness</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an
appearance of truth that is false or deceptive; seeming
plausibility.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> speciousness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>tasteless showiness.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flashiness, garishness, gaudiness, loudness,
tawdriness, glitz.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merganser</ent>⟦br⟧
